大多数餐厅都设有公司创办人哈兰德·桑德斯上校的图像<ref name="autogenerated51"/>除了店内食用以及外带，许多独立式肯德基餐厅也提供[[得来速|得来速]]的选择。<ref name="Cartwright2003">{{cite book|last=Cartwright|first=Roger|title=Implementing a Training and Development Strategy: Training and Development 11.8|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qyGeqgh8NowC&pg=PA42|date=2003-10-31|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-84112-494-0|page=42|access-date=2014-03-24|archive-date=2014-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103071841/http://books.google.com/books?id=qyGeqgh8NowC&pg=PA42|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

肯德基在少量市场也提供有限送外卖服务<ref name="Cartwright2003"/>。

全球每天平均在每家肯德基餐厅有250个订单，大都发生在2小时的高峰时段。<ref name="Balakrishnan132">{{cite book|last=Stephens Balakrishnan|first=Melodena|title=East Meets West: the World is Round and Time is Cyclic|year=2013|publisher=Emerald Group Publishing|isbn=978-1-78190-413-8|pages=126–132|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8CLmuucAqogC&pg=PA126|access-date=2016-04-04|archive-date=2015-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321191030/http://books.google.com/books?id=8CLmuucAqogC&pg=PA126|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[贩售亭|贩售亭]]设有限定菜单，在非传统地点如加油站、[[便利店|便利店]]、[[体育场|体育场]]、[[主题公园|主题公园]]、[[學院_(學校)|学院]]经营，而这在一间全面的分店并不实际。<ref name="Cartwright2003"/>

==各地的情況==
===美國===
根据{{lang|en|Technomic}}的预算，肯德基2013年在美国的销售量为42亿2000万[[美元|美元]]。<ref name=fila>{{cite news|last=Wong|first=Venessa|title=Chick-fil-A Stole KFC's Chicken Crown With a Fraction of the Stores|url=http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-03-28/chick-fil-a-stole-kfcs-chicken-crown-with-a-fraction-of-the-stores|accessdate=2014-03-30|newspaper=Businessweek|date=2014-03-28|archive-date=2014-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330033327/http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-03-28/chick-fil-a-stole-kfcs-chicken-crown-with-a-fraction-of-the-stores|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[File:Kfc_taco_bell.jpg|thumb]]的奥斯科达[[非建制地區|非建制地區]]（{{lang|en|Oscoda}}）的肯德基–塔可鐘联名品牌]]
肯德基在美国的基本特色是物价低廉、菜单有限（平均有29项）、强调外带。<ref name="autogenerated5"/>许多肯德基餐厅与[[塔可鐘|塔可鐘]]、[[必胜客|必胜客]]或其他百胜餐厅位于同一地点。<ref name="Cartwright2003"/>当百胜拥有[[海滋客|海滋客]]以及[[艾德熊|艾德熊]]时，这些快餐店也经常与肯德基位于同一地点。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=DSNB&d_place=DSNB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F37F1EBCB5C5B9A&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title=Partnering for success,  Firms finding that co-branding makes economic sense|date=2002-01-13|work=Deseret News|accessdate=2013-04-19|archive-date=2013-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508161754/http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=DSNB&d_place=DSNB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F37F1EBCB5C5B9A&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|dead-url=no}}</ref>这些地点往往显得如同同一家餐厅，提供包含来自两家快餐店的食品的菜单。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2005/07/11/business/11yum.html |title=Diners Walk Through One Door and Visit Two Restaurants |author=Warner, Melanie |work=New York Times |date=2005-07-11 |accessdate=2007-12-29 |quote=Yum's multibranded stores have two illuminated logos, but they function as one restaurant. They have combined kitchens, a single line of cashiers and a staff trained to prepare both sets of menu items. |archive-date=2011-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110617003832/http://www.nytimes.com/2005/07/11/business/11yum.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>截至2003年，美国拥有354家肯德基–塔可鐘联合餐厅，提供肯德基和塔可鐘的快餐，有13家提供肯德基完整菜单以及限量的必胜客食品。<ref name="Cartwright2003"/>这个概念源自于1991年，当时[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]]开设一家肯德基–塔可鐘联合餐厅。<ref name="Darden1"/>某些地点是以结合肯德基、塔可鐘和必胜客开张的，但这未能成功，百胜首席执行官大卫·诺瓦克则怪罪于缺乏特许经营商的承诺。<ref name="Novak2012">{{cite book|last=Novak|first=David|title=Taking People with You: The Only Way to Make Big Things Happen|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=4vEiAHlWfToC|accessdate=2013-03-11|date=2012-01-26|publisher=Penguin Books, Limited|isbn=978-0-241-95413-3|archive-date=2013-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130530050001/http://books.google.com/books?id=4vEiAHlWfToC|dead-url=no}}</ref>

起初，桑德斯与肯德基使用[[氢化植物油|氢化植物油]]来炸鸡，但是，1980年代，公司开始转而使用廉价食用油，如[[棕櫚油|棕櫚油]]或[[大豆油|大豆油]]。<ref>{{Youtube|id=cF4ph_gKcpI|title=Colonel Sanders shows Tennesse Ernie Ford & Minnie Pearl how he cooks his KFC chicken}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=KFCJ 'does chicken right' – for Japan's tastes |url=http://business.highbeam.com/409700/article-1G1-6827144/kfcj-does-chicken-right-japan-tastes |newspaper=Nation's Restaurant News |date=1988-11-14 |accessdate=2012-06-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508190044/http://business.highbeam.com/409700/article-1G1-6827144/kfcj-does-chicken-right-japan-tastes |archive-date=2013-05-08 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>2000年代，这些食用油的[[反式脂肪|反式脂肪]]含量相对较高变得明显，而反式脂肪会增加心脏疾病的风险。截至2007年4月，公司所有美国分店改用无反式脂肪的大豆油。<ref>{{cite news|title=KFC, Taco Bell finish switch to trans-fat-free oil|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/18383687/ns/health-diet_and_nutrition/t/kfc-taco-bell-finish-switch-trans-fat-free-oil/#.UQp1Eyc03K1|accessdate=2013-01-18|newspaper=NBC News|date=2007-04-30|archive-date=2013-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130329014346/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/18383687/ns/health-diet_and_nutrition/t/kfc-taco-bell-finish-switch-trans-fat-free-oil#.UQp1Eyc03K1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2008年，诺瓦克说，肯德基在美国的销售量低，是因为缺乏新点子和新菜单。<ref name=courierlow>{{cite news|last=Davis|first=Alex|title=Yum chief Novak takes on KFC's weak results|url=http://www.courier-journal.com/article/20080717/BUSINESS/80717019/Yum-chief-Novak-takes-KFC-s-weak-results?nclick_check=1 {{subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-09-27|newspaper=Courier Journal|date=2008-07-17}}</ref>2009年春季推出的肯德基烤鸡仅暂时停止销售量下滑。<ref name=autogenerated23>{{cite news | url=http://money.cnn.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive/1997/08/04/229716/index.htm | work=CNN | first=Patricia | last=Sellers | title=Pepsi's Eateries Go It Alone Tricon: Lousy Name, Excellent Management | date=1997-08-04 | accessdate=2013-09-27 | archive-date=2014-05-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512231459/http://money.cnn.com/magazines/fortune/fortune_archive/1997/08/04/229716/index.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>2010年，肯德基宣布复兴计划，包括改善餐厅经营、推出价值食品，以及在菜单上提供更健康的选择。<ref name="autogenerated23"/>同年，《[[广告时代|广告时代]]》（{{lang|en|''Advertising Age''}}）指出，肯德基正因为其规模较小的竞争对手{{lang|en|[[Chick-fil-A|Chick-fil-A]]}}，而失去市场份额。<ref>{{cite news|last=Bryson|first=Emily|title=KFC's stunts make nightly news, but do nothing to stop sales slide|newspaper=Advertising Age|date=2010-04-19}}</ref>2011年，[[彭博新闻|彭博新闻]]称肯德基美国为“败给麦当劳股份有限公司”。<ref>{{cite news|last=Mellor|first=William|title=McDonald's No Match For KFC In China As Colonel Rules Fast Food|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-26/mcdonald-s-no-match-for-kfc-in-china-where-colonel-sanders-rules-fast-food.html|newspaper=Bloomberg News|date=2011-01-26|accessdate=2013-09-27|archive-date=2013-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822175534/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-26/mcdonald-s-no-match-for-kfc-in-china-where-colonel-sanders-rules-fast-food.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2012年，杂志《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》形容多个肯德基分店“老套、不吸引人”，公司也“很久没有推出有趣的新食品了。”<ref>{{cite news|last=Tice|first=Carol|title=Why Popeyes is Buying Up Bankrupt KFC Restaurants|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/caroltice/2012/10/25/popeyes-buys-up-bankrupt-kfc-restaurants/|accessdate=2013-01-28|newspaper=Forbes|date=2012-10-25|archive-date=2013-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208170650/http://www.forbes.com/sites/caroltice/2012/10/25/popeyes-buys-up-bankrupt-kfc-restaurants/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年，《[[彭博商业周刊|彭博商业周刊]]》形容，肯德基在发展中地区，特别是非洲、中国和印度，是个“强有力的选手”，然而在美国却被竞争对手如{{lang|en|Chick-fil-A}}、[[大力水手炸雞|大力水手炸雞]]打败，致使肯德基的市场份额下降。<ref name=autogenerated21 /><ref name="autogenerated21">{{cite news|first=Associated Press|title=Colonel's Secret Recipe Gets Bodyguards|url=http://www.cnbc.com/id/26618866/Colonel039s_Secret_Recipe_Gets_Bodyguards|accessdate=2013-01-31|newspaper=CNBC|date=2008-09-09|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923032226/http://www.cnbc.com/id/26618866/Colonel039s_Secret_Recipe_Gets_Bodyguards|archivedate=2013-09-23}}</ref>有分析师推测肯德基将在美国关门大吉。<ref name="autogenerated21"/>同年，公司开始出售公司持有的美国餐厅给特许经营商经营，有意将公司总体持有的分店从35%减至5%。<ref name="autogenerated21"/>

===英国===
[[File:KFC,_Belfast,_June_2010.JPG|thumb]][[贝尔法斯特|贝尔法斯特市]]的肯德基]]
截至2013年，英国有784家肯德基餐厅。<ref name=restcount/>大约70%由特许经营商经营，其余为公司持有。<ref name=shukerinterview2014>{{cite news|last=Cave|first=Andrew|title=Fast food and appetite for growth suits veteran KFC boss just fine|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/retailandconsumer/10791472/KFC-boss-Martin-Shuker-has-an-appetite-for-finger-lickin-food-and-growth.html|accessdate=2014-04-28|newspaper=Daily Telegraph|date=2014-04-28|archive-date=2014-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530141337/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/retailandconsumer/10791472/KFC-boss-Martin-Shuker-has-an-appetite-for-finger-lickin-food-and-growth.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>公司雇用了2万4000名员工。<ref name=shukerinterview2014/>大约400家为得來速设备。<ref name=shukerinterview2014/>分店平均营业额为100万至150万[[英镑|英镑]]之间。<ref name=shukerinterview2014/>

常年销售等于6万公吨的鸡，有60%是采购自英国四大供应商，包括[[法琴达集团|法琴达集团]]（{{lang|en|Faccenda Group}}）<ref name=faccenda>{{cite news|last=Machell|first=Ben|title=Nando’s: the A-list’s favourite food|url={{cite news|last=Machell|first=Ben|title=Nando’s: the A-list’s favourite food|url={{cite news|last=Machell|first=Ben|title=Nando’s: the A-list’s favourite food|url={{cite news|last=Machell|first=Ben|title=Nando’s: the A-list’s favourite food|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/celebrity/article3849309.ece {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-08-22|newspaper=The Times|date=2013-08-22|archive-date=2013-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822105830/http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/celebrity/article3849309.ece|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-08-22|newspaper=The Times|date=2013-08-22|archive-date=2013-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822105830/http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/celebrity/article3849309.ece|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-08-22|newspaper=The Times|date=2013-08-22|archive-date=2013-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822105830/http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/celebrity/article3849309.ece|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-08-22|newspaper=The Times|date=2013-08-22}}</ref>和[[两姐妹食品集团|两姐妹食品集团]]（{{lang|en|2 Sisters Food Group}}）<ref>{{cite news|last=Shanahan|first=Andrew|title=Anatomy of a dish|url=http://www.theguardian.com/news/2005/oct/28/food.lifeandhealth|accessdate=2013-01-06|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2005-10-28|archive-date=2013-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003224325/http://www.theguardian.com/news/2005/oct/28/food.lifeandhealth|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Stiff|first=Peter|title=Chickens and Fox's reap rewards|newspaper=The Times|date=2011-07-06}}</ref>，并每周至少三次新鲜分发到各分店。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fast food chicken arrives frozen on the slow boat |author=Robert Mendick and Ben Leach |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/foodanddrinknews/7386214/Fast-food-chicken-arrives-frozen-on-the-slow-boat.html |newspaper=The Sunday Telegraph (London) |date=2010-03-06 |accessdate=2012-06-30 |archive-date=2011-08-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110828134221/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/foodanddrink/foodanddrinknews/7386214/Fast-food-chicken-arrives-frozen-on-the-slow-boat.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>其余40%采购自欧洲、泰国（包括{{link-en|卜蜂食品|Charoen Pokphand Foods}}）和巴西公司。<ref name=autogenerated18>{{cite news | url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/sep/10/business/fi-kfc10 | work=Los Angeles Times | title=KFC on lookout for fowl play | date=2008-09-10 | accessdate=2013-09-27 | archive-date=2014-04-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407125324/http://articles.latimes.com/2008/sep/10/business/fi-kfc10 | dead-url=no }}</ref>所有原始配方的鸡是在英国国内采购的。<ref name="autogenerated18"/>

1965年5月，[[英格兰|英格兰]]在[[西北英格蘭|西北部]]的[[普雷斯顿|普雷斯顿]]开设肯德基第一家海外分店，是英格兰第一家美式连锁快餐公司，将近十年后麦当劳、[[漢堡王|漢堡王]]以及必胜客才到来。<ref>{{cite news |author=Douglas, Torin|title=How Kentucky Fried Chicken plan to fly back up the pecking order|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_financial-times_1983-06-06_71_52/page/19|newspaper=The Times |date=1983-06-21 |page=19}}</ref>1968年11月，[[北芬奇利|北芬奇利]]（{{lang|en|North Finchley}}）增设第一家[[伦敦|伦敦]]分店。<ref name=londonkfc>{{cite web|title=Eating Out 1950–2000|url=http://www.20thcenturylondon.org.uk/eating-out-1950-2000|publisher=20th Century London|accessdate=2013-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213525/http://www.20thcenturylondon.org.uk/eating-out-1950-2000|archive-date=2013-10-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>肯德基从1971年的31间分店，增至1975年的250间分店。<ref name=nov75>{{cite news|title=Business Around the World|newspaper=US News & World Report|date=1975-11-03}}</ref>1970年代末期以及1980年代，各餐厅开始引进座位。肯德基于1984年在英国开设第一家得来速餐厅。<ref>{{cite book|title=Hotels & Restaurants International|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=fb5aAAAAYAAJ|accessdate=2013-08-19|year=1984|publisher=Restaurants & Institutions Magazine|page=107|archive-date=2013-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012210106/http://books.google.com/books?id=fb5aAAAAYAAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>1987年为止，公司有将近400间分店。<ref name="JacobsScholliers2003">{{cite book|author1=Marc Jacobs|author2=Peter Scholliers|title=Eating Out in Europe: Picnics, Gourmet Dining and Snacks Since the Late Eighteenth Century|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0AYbEC2xNSoC&pg=PA307|accessdate=2013-08-19|date=June 2003|publisher=Berg|isbn=978-1-85973-658-6|page=307|archive-date=2013-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012220410/http://books.google.com/books?id=0AYbEC2xNSoC&pg=PA307|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===日本===
[[File:池袋_(15580953844).jpg|thumb]]期间，东京[[池袋|池袋]]的一间肯德基餐厅，可见门口张贴的圣诞套餐宣传海报]]
日本是继中国和美国后，肯德基的第三大市场，设有1200间分店。<ref name=yumstores>{{cite web|title=Top 25 Markets — Traditional Stores (Year-End 2012)|url=http://yum.com/investors/restcounts.asp|publisher=Yum! Brands|accessdate=2013-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202153644/http://www.yum.com/investors/restcounts.asp|archive-date=2017-02-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>在日本，有70%的销售额是外带，顾客倾向于买炸鸡来举办庆祝会以及其他特殊场合，将它作为小菜。<ref name=tanikawa>{{cite news|last=Tanikawa|first=Miki|title=Fried Chicken Dilemma Is Puzzler for KFC Japan|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/18/your-money/18iht-mkfc_ed3_.html|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=New York Times|date=2001-08-18|archive-date=2013-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005022822/http://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/18/your-money/18iht-mkfc_ed3_.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

肯德基日本原本是美国总公司与日本的[[三菱商事|三菱商事]][[合资公司|合资]]形成的。<ref name=mitsubishi>{{cite web|title=KFC Japan|url=http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/|publisher=Mitsubishi Corporation|accessdate=2013-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622165235/http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/|archive-date=2013-06-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>经过四年的谈判，三菱获得经营日本肯德基的特许经营权，并于1970年3月在[[1970年世界博览会|大阪世界博览会]]上开了一家试验餐厅。<ref name=mitsubishi />证明成功后，1970年11月，第一家正式餐厅于[[名古屋市|名古屋市]]的[[郊区|郊区]]开业。<ref name=mitsubishi2>{{cite web|title=KFC Japan|url=http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/page2.html|publisher=Mitsubishi Corporation|accessdate=2013-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511114128/http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/page2.html|archive-date=2013-05-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>美国总公司希望在郊区营业，但三菱却认为应该在市中心开办分店，因为当时日本并未广泛运行汽车。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>大阪市再增设两家餐厅，但由于分店正挣扎于营业，少于一年，日本的肯德基已亏损1亿[[日圆|日圆]]。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>因为这次的亏损，三菱转而按原定计划在市区开设餐厅。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>

1972年，第一家新策略分店于[[神户市|神户市]]开门营业，神户市是西方侨民聚集地的高档市场。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>新策略取得成功，1973年为止增设了100间分店。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>1974年12月，肯德基日本开始推行炸鸡作为[[圣诞|圣诞]]餐。<ref name=mitsubishi2/>自那时起，在圣诞节期间吃肯德基成为日本广泛实行的习俗，在日本的肯德基圣诞节套餐甚至需提前数周预订。<ref name=xmas>{{cite news|last=Whipp|first=Lindsay|title=All Japan wants for Christmas is Kentucky Fried Chicken|url={{cite news|last=Whipp|first=Lindsay|title=All Japan wants for Christmas is Kentucky Fried Chicken|url={{cite news|last=Whipp|first=Lindsay|title=All Japan wants for Christmas is Kentucky Fried Chicken|url={{cite news|last=Whipp|first=Lindsay|title=All Japan wants for Christmas is Kentucky Fried Chicken|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2dafc6-0ba4-11e0-a313-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2XRv8gnig {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Financial Times|date=2010-12-19|archive-date=2013-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529212106/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2dafc6-0ba4-11e0-a313-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2XRv8gnig|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Financial Times|date=2010-12-19|archive-date=2013-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529212106/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2dafc6-0ba4-11e0-a313-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2XRv8gnig|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}}|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Financial Times|date=2010-12-19|archive-date=2013-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529212106/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2dafc6-0ba4-11e0-a313-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2XRv8gnig|dead-url=no}} {{Subscription required}} |accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Financial Times|date=2010-12-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Eric Barton|url=http://www.bbc.com/capital/story/20161216-why-japan-celebrates-christmas-with-kfc|title=Why Japan celebrates Christmas with KFC|work=BBC Capital|date=2016-12-19|accessdate=2017-08-06|archive-date=2017-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805234707/http://www.bbc.com/capital/story/20161216-why-japan-celebrates-christmas-with-kfc|dead-url=no}}</ref>哈兰德·桑德斯本人曾于1972年、1978年和1980年亲自走访日本的肯德基。<ref name=japancolonel>{{cite web|title=Colonel's Story|url=http://www.kfc.co.jp/room/story.html|work=KFC Japan|publisher=Yum!|accessdate=2013-11-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113151907/http://www.kfc.co.jp/room/story.html|archivedate=2013-11-13}}</ref>

1990年8月，肯德基日本列于[[东京证券交易所|东京证券交易所]]。<ref name=autogenerated87>{{cite web|title=KFC Japan|url=http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/page3.html|publisher=Mitsubishi Corporation|accessdate=2013-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511123102/http://www.mitsubishicorp.com/jp/en/mclibrary/projectstory/vol02/page3.html|archive-date=2013-05-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>肯德基从1980年代日本的经济增长中获益，但是快餐店迅速扩张，使各特许经营商互相抢夺市场份额，致使1990年代中期有大约100间分店关门大吉。<ref name=lajapan>{{cite news|title=Competition Gains on Colonel Sanders in Japan|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1995-08-14/business/fi-34960_1_fried-chicken|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=1995-08-14|archive-date=2013-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113150530/http://articles.latimes.com/1995-08-14/business/fi-34960_1_fried-chicken|dead-url=no}}</ref>2000年，据肯德基日本报告，其销售额将近5亿9800万美元。<ref name="Karan2010">{{cite book|last=Karan|first=Pradyumna|title=Japan in the 21st Century: Environment, Economy, and Society|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=IgOTn0gdmPoC&pg=PA330|date=2010-09-12|publisher=University Press of Kentucky|isbn=978-0-8131-2763-7|page=330|access-date=2016-04-04|archive-date=2015-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321191812/http://books.google.com/books?id=IgOTn0gdmPoC&pg=PA330|dead-url=no}}</ref>2007年12月，三菱在一次148亿3000万日圆的交易假定对肯德基日本的主要控制权。<ref name=jt>{{cite news|title=Mitsubishi takes over Kentucky Fried Chicken Japan for ¥14.83 billion|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/12/09/business/mitsubishi-takes-over-kentucky-fried-chicken-japan-for-14-83-billion/#.Uc8qVvnVDK0|accessdate=2013-06-29|newspaper=Japan Times|date=2007-12-09|archive-date=2013-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113151849/http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/12/09/business/mitsubishi-takes-over-kentucky-fried-chicken-japan-for-14-83-billion/#.Uc8qVvnVDK0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

